The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 15: The Reserve Bank of India may take monetary action to tame the rising prices ahead of the scheduled review of the policy on July 27, deputy governor K.C. Chakrabarty said. Wholesale price-based inflation provisionally touched a 19-month high of 10.16 per cent in May, while final figures released for March put inflation at 11.04 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, June 15: Users of Reliance Industries natural gas from the Krishna-Godavari fields will pay transport charges in the range of Rs 15 per million British thermal unit (mBtu) to Rs 60.94 per mBtu depending on the distance of their plants from the Andhra Pradesh coast.                             
	 Mumbai, June 15: Corporate Indias advance tax payments have jumped sharply in the April-June quarter of this fiscal, mirroring the uptick in the economy.                             
	 New Delhi, June 15: State-run oil firms have raised ATF prices by over 1.7 per cent, in line with the rising trend in global oil prices. ATF rates in Delhi have been raised Rs 688 to Rs 40,192 per kilolitre effective midnight tonight.                            
	 Calcutta, June 15: Adobe Systems plans to offer its latest suite of softwares on a subscription basis. The firm is also considering adopting the pay-per-use model in the emerging markets.
                                                                                                                          
